data.comment: The match has started.
Throw-in for Goteborg close to the penalty box.
In the minute 3, Malmo have been given a penalty at Stadion...
It's advantage Malmo in Malmo as Anders Christiansen scores from the spot to make it 1-0.
Throw-in Malmo.
In the minute 5, A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Malmo are pushing forward but Erdal Rakip's finish is wide of the goal.
Goal kick for Goteborg at Stadion.
In the minute 7, Ball safe as Goteborg is awarded a throw-in in their half.
In Malmo, Goteborg push forward quickly but are pulled up for offside.
Throw-in for Goteborg at Stadion.
In the minute 9, Victor Wolf signals a throw-in for Malmo, close to Goteborg's area.
Goteborg awarded a free kick in their own half.
Free kick for Malmo in the half of Goteborg.
In the minute 14, Malmo drive upfield and Ola Toivonen gets in a shot. The strike is blocked by a Goteborg defender.
Victor Wolf signals a Malmo throw-in in Goteborg's half.
Throw-in for Goteborg in their own half.
In the minute 16, Free kick Malmo.
Ola Toivonen of Malmo smashes in a shot on target. The keeper saves, though.
Free kick for Goteborg in their own half.
In the minute 21, It's a goal kick for the home team in Malmo.
Goteborg to take a throw-in in Malmo territory.
Goteborg's Patrik Karlsson Lagemyr breaks free at Stadion. But the strike goes wide of the post.
In the minute 22, Victor Wolf awards Malmo a goal kick.
Can Goteborg get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Malmo's half?
Goal! Goteborg go level at 1-1 through Pontus Wernbloom in Malmo.
In the minute 24, Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Malmo.
In Malmo a free kick has been awarded the home team.
August Erlingmark (Goteborg) has received a yellow card from Victor Wolf.
In the minute 26, Malmo pushes forward through Ola Toivonen, whose finish on goal is saved.
Throw-in for Malmo in the half of Goteborg.
Malmo have been awarded a corner by Victor Wolf.
In the minute 27, Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Malmo in their own half.
Victor Wolf awards the away team a throw-in.
Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Malmo in their own half.
In the minute 29, Goteborg drive forward at breakneck speed but are pulled up for offside.
Malmo awarded a free kick in their own half.
Free kick for Goteborg in the half of Malmo.
In the minute 31, Malmo awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Giorgi Kharaishvili is back on his feet again.
Play has been temporarily suspended for attention to Giorgi Kharaishvili for Goteborg who is writhing in pain on the pitch.
In the minute 33, Malmo are in shooting range from this free kick.
Anel Ahmedhodzic (Malmo) strikes at Stadion but his header is cleared.
Free kick for Goteborg in their own half.
In the minute 35, Goal! Ola Toivonen gives Malmo a 2-1 lead in Malmo.
Great play from Adi Nalic to set up the goal.
Can Malmo get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Goteborg's half?
In the minute 38, Malmo are too eager and fall into an offside trap.
Throw-in Malmo.
Victor Wolf signals a Malmo throw-in in Goteborg's half.
In the minute 41, Corner awarded to Malmo.
Malmo are caught offside.
Ball goes out of play for a Goteborg goal kick.
In the minute 44, The match has been stopped briefly for attention to the injured Soren Rieks.
Soren Rieks is back on the pitch.
Goteborg push upfield but Victor Wolf quickly pulls them for offside.
In the minute 45, The 1st half is prolonged by 2 minutes of added time.
Can Goteborg capitalize from this throw-in deep inside Malmo's half?
Malmo awarded a throw-in in their own half.
In the minute 45, The first half has been concluded at Stadion.
The second-half is now underway.
Jon Dahl Tomasson is making the team's first substitution at Stadion with Isaac Thelin replacing Adi Nalic.
In the minute 47, Goteborg have a goal kick.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Malmo.
Goal kick for Malmo at Stadion.
In the minute 50, A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
Goteborg awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 52, Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Goteborg.
Throw-in for Malmo at Stadion.
Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Goteborg in their own half.
In the minute 55, Malmo to take a throw-in in Goteborg territory.
Malmo are whistled for offside.
Ball safe as Malmo is awarded a throw-in in their half.
In the minute 57, Malmo's Isaac Thelin goes close with his head but his effort is blocked.
Throw-in for Goteborg in their own half.
Throw-in for Goteborg in the half of Malmo.
In the minute 59, Giorgi Kharaishvili of Goteborg gets in a strike, but is off target.
Malmo have a goal kick.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
In the minute 60, Victor Wolf awards the home team a throw-in.
Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Malmo in their own half.
Malmo push forward at Stadion and Isaac Thelin gets in a strike. This is blocked, however, by a determined Goteborg defence.
Corner awarded to Malmo.
In the minute 63, Jon Dahl Tomasson (Malmo) is making a second substitution, with Bonke Innocent replacing Arnor Traustason.
It's now 3-1 thanks to an own goal from Giorgi Kharaishvili.
In the minute 65, Victor Wolf awards the away team a throw-in.
Victor Wolf awards Goteborg a goal kick.
Goteborg's Giorgi Kharaishvili gets in a shot on goal at Stadion. But the effort is unsuccessful.
In the minute 67, Goteborg have been awarded a corner by Victor Wolf.
Goteborg to take a throw-in in Malmo territory.
Robin Soder is replacing Pontus Wernbloom for the away team.
In the minute 68, The away team have replaced Giorgi Kharaishvili with Sargon Abraham. This is the second substitution made today by Ferran Sibila Pont.
Robin Soder for Goteborg is whistled offside.
Goteborg awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 70, Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
Goteborg needs to be cautious. Malmo have an attacking throw-in.
Ball goes out of play for a Goteborg goal kick.
In the minute 72, Throw-in for Goteborg in their own half.
Victor Wolf signals a free kick to Malmo in their own half.
Malmo awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 77, Can Goteborg get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Malmo's half?
In the minute 78, Free kick for Malmo in their own half.
The away team replace Yahya Kalley with Amin Affane.
Emil Holm is on a sub for Alhassan Yusuf for Goteborg.
At Stadion, Robin Soder has been yellow-carded for the away team.
Victor Wolf signals a Malmo throw-in in Goteborg's half.
In the minute 80, Throw-in for Malmo in the half of Goteborg.
Malmo awarded a throw-in in their own half.
In Malmo Goteborg drive forward through Hosam Aiesh. His shot is on target but it's saved.
In the minute 82, Erdal Rakip is down and play has been interrupted for a few moments.
Malmo's Erdal Rakip is back in action after a slight knock.
Free kick Malmo.
In the minute 84, Rasmus Bengtsson is replacing Ola Toivonen for Malmo at Stadion.
The home team have replaced Erdal Rakip with Amin Sarr. This is the fourth substitution made today by Jon Dahl Tomasson.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
In the minute 86, In Malmo a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Ball safe as Goteborg is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Throw-in Goteborg.
In the minute 89, Throw-in high up the field for Goteborg in Malmo.
Goteborg have a goal kick.
At Stadion, Goteborg are penalized for being offside.
4 minutes of injury time will be added to the 2nd half.
Ball goes out of play for a Malmo goal kick.
Goteborg have been awarded a corner by Victor Wolf.
Throw-in for Goteborg at Stadion.
Malmo to take a throw-in in Goteborg territory.
Victor Wolf blows to end the match. The final score is 3-1.
